  overviewText="Gum disease (periodontal disease) is a bacterial infection that begins in the tissue surrounding your teeth and progresses — if untreated — to destroy the bone that holds them in place. Early-stage gingivitis causes redness, swelling, and bleeding but is fully reversible with professional treatment. Advanced periodontitis involves bone loss, deep pockets between teeth and gums, and is the number one reason adults lose teeth — not cavities. The good news: with proper treatment and consistent maintenance, we can stop the progression and preserve your teeth for life."
  overviewExtra="A significant portion of adults in Bayside, Whitestone, Fresh Meadows, and the surrounding Queens neighborhoods have some form of gum disease without knowing it — because it rarely causes pain in its early stages. At Thrive Dental, every comprehensive exam includes gum pocket measurements that detect periodontal disease before it becomes visible. If we find signs of infection, we'll walk you through the findings, explain the stage of disease, and outline a treatment plan — whether that means a deep cleaning, laser therapy, or a referral to our periodontal specialist. We do not just monitor gum disease: we treat it aggressively and then maintain the results with a customized recall schedule."
